Email:colon[] <A href=mailto:colon[]acm_europe@acm.org>acm_europe@acm.org</A>
</UL>

<h2>Microfilm and Microfiche</h2>
Microfilm editions from 1976 through 1982 can be purchased from the following
address.
<UL>
Microfilm Department<br>
Waverly Press<br>
428 East Preston Street<br>
Baltimore, MD 21202
</UL>

Microfiche editions through 1982 can be
purchased from the following address.
<UL>
Kraus Microform Route 100<br>
Millwood, NY 10546
</UL>

Microfilm and microfiche editions are also available from the adress given
below.
<UL>
University Microfilms International<br>
300 North Zeeb Road<br>
Department PR<br>
Ann Arbor, M1 48106
</UL>

When payment is included with subscriptions, membership applications, 
or renewal notices, use the following address.
<UL>
ACM<br>
P.O. Box 12105<br>
Church Street Station<br>
New York, NY 10249
</UL>

See the top line of mailing label for subscription expiration date coded 
in four digits: the first two are the year, the last two the month of 
expiration.

You may 
<A HREF="http://acm.org/catalog/journals/109.html">subscribe</A>
to ACM :journalAcronym[] or 
<A HREF="http://acm.org/catalog/journals/109.html">obtain</A>
copies of individual issues or back volumes.

<P>

<h2>Address Changes and Requests for Membership Applications and
Information</h2>
 
Notices of address changes and requests for membership applications and 
subscription information should be sent to the following address.
<UL>
ACM<br>
1515 Broadway<br>
New York, NY 10036
</UL>

Allow 6-8 weeks tor change of name and address or 
new membership to become effective.  Send old label with new address 
notification. To avoid interruption of service, notify your local post office 
before change of residence; for a fee, the post office will forward 
second and third class periodicals.
